      "content": "but if \"inclusivity and respect for diverse voices\" is the only way to make it not dangerous, doesn't that mean any real nationalism—the kind that actually prioritizes the interests of one specific group or culture—is fundamentally flawed? it feels like you're saying nationalism is only \"good\" when it's basically just multiculturalism with a different name.",
